"https://lccn.loc.gov/sh89005046"><summary>Miscellaneous collection of poems mostly by the poet Tajallī Shīrāzī (d. 1085/1674). Volume not dated. Scribal shikastah āmīz and taʿlīq, by multiple hands. Annotations. Not foliated. Lacking original binding. Paper dust wrapper. Folios unbound; severely cropped, wormholes, creased, stained, later repairs. Condition very fragile. Erased ownership marks.</summary><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1370-item1"><locus from="1v" to="5v">ff. 1v-5v</locus><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><note><p>Delhi Persian 1370a.</p><p>Brief untitled selection of eulogies or manqabat in praise of the Caliph and Imam ʿAlī in tarkībband form by the poet Mīrzā ʿAlī Riz̤āʾ ibn Ḥusayn Shīrāzī takhalluṣ Tajallī (d. 1085/1674).</p><p>Text in two columns without rulings.</p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><author><persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100167332134.0x000001 viaf_294571435">Tajallī</persName><persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_294571435">تجلي</persName></author></msItem><msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1370-item2"><locus from="6r" to="8r">ff. 6r-8r</locus><author /><note><p>Delhi Persian 1370b.</p><p>Annotations by an unnamed scribe comprised of selected quatrains or rubāʿīyāt by various poets, including Mīrzā Sanjar, ʿAbd al-Vāḥid, Ẓahīr, Hindī, Khayyām, and Ṭāhirī.</p><p>Text in six columns in alternating oblique and vertical orientations, without rulings.</p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><note /></msItem><msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1370-item3"><author><persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_294571435">Tajallī</persName><persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_294571435">تجلي</persName></author><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20186">Miʿrāj al-khayāl</title><title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20186">معراج الخيال</title><note><p>Delhi Persian 1370c.</p><p>Fragment from the opening of the mas̲navī on divine love by the poet Mīrzā ʿAlī Riz̤āʾ ibn Ḥusayn Shīrāzī takhalluṣ Tajallī (d. 1085/1674).</p><p>This copy is defective, as suggested by the presence of a catchword and the lack of further folios.</p><p>Text in two columns without rulings.</p><p>Not dated at end.</p></note><textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang><note /></msItem></msContents><physDesc><objectDesc form="codex"><supportDesc material="chart"><extent>8 ff. 
